Job Description:
Overall Purpose
- To lead Vattanac Bank’s legal strategy and framework to protect the Bank’s property and interests and support Management to ensure legal compliance and effective business operations.

Responsibilities: 
- Manage legal issues and protection of the Bank’s property and interest;
- Oversee legal issues regarding terms and protection clauses of the Bank’s contracts and other legal documents;
- Oversee legal function related to the protection of the Bank’s property and interest against errors, employees’ fault and management;
- Provide advice and ensure compliance with the relevant law and regulations to ensure high standards of legal compliance are practiced in the bank;
- Advise, vet the draft legal documents, give training on legal matters, as well as set out and assist other departments with formulation of policy and procedures to ensure legal compliance;
- Design, implement and maintain high quality compliance programs for Vattanac Bank to promote a culture that enables Vattanac Bank to efficiently meet its regulatory obligations and bank’s policies;
- Assess legal advice for business in regard to issues in the Bank’s daily operations;
- Assist the Bank to achieve their objectives by providing quality, timely, commercially relevant and cost effective legal service and compliance supports to minimize risk of compliance breaches;
- Escalate issues to management team and provide effective recommendations and implementation of compliant solutions;
- Manage the work performed by external lawyers (if applicable) to ensure the bank gets high quality services on competitive prices;

Job Requirement:
- Bachelors or Masters Degree in Law with excellent legal background (Cambodia and international);
- Sound knowledge of the bank’s business and operations, preferably gained through at least 3 years of general banking experience;
- Experience in legal advisory handling matters relating to corporate and commercial;
- Superior communication, leadership, organizational, interpersonal, written, verbal and analytical skills
- Sound knowledge of and great sensitivity to business and social issues;
- Good understanding of civil procedure, court process, banking laws as well as regulatory and governmental relations;
- Good command of spoken and written English.

